main event: An unidentified aerial object was sighted in Albuquerque, New Mexico on 24th February 1950 at different times and locations by multiple witnesses.
interesting points: The object was observed by experienced weather observers and was considered reliable by co-workers and colleagues.
The object appeared to be very far away at an elevation of about 20° to 25° and was observed for several minutes by the witnesses.
The object's characteristics included a round shape with no apparent means of support, no sound, no trail or exhaust, and no light or luminosity detected.

One observer described the object as being the size of the dark portion of the moon and having no apparent means of support or projections/indentations, while another observer described it as bright white with no reflections, sound, or trail.
All logical leads were exhausted, and the case was closed with the object remaining unidentified.
witnesses: experienced weather observers, Mr. and Mrs. R. S. Prio, Jr., Mr. McDONALD, Mr. __________
